      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. The students should be a native of Rajasthan state.\n1. Applicant students should belong to the following Other Backward Classes, that must have been issued by Tehsildar or a higher-level revenue officer.\n\n   1. Banjara, Baladiya, Labana. \n   1. Gadia-Lohar, Gadolia.\n   1. Gujar, Gurjar. \n   1. Raika, Raibari (Debasi).\n   1. Gadariya (Gadri), Gayari.\n\n1.  The annual income of the parents/guardian of the applicant from all sources (including the candidate&#39;s own income, if any) should be up to Rs.2,50,000 (Rupees two lakh fifty thousand in words). \n1. An employed student who studies as a full-time student by taking leave without pay during the entire course will be eligible for the scholarship.\n1. All the children of the same parent/guardian will be eligible to benefit from this scheme.\n\n",
